From 7cb16c3b70f6d9eea78d6e09f6f85e87be4570b0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vasu Bhatia <git@vbh.ai>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 12:59:26 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] eink: add auto-brightness curve editor
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Three independent piecewise-linear curves (cold / warm / keyboard)
defined at the same eight lux breakpoints (0, 5, 30, 100, 300, 1000,
3000, 8000). Each (curve, lux) pair persists to a Settings.System key
that the SystemUI EinkAutoBrightnessController reads at runtime, so
edits take effect on the next sensor tick without a service restart.

UI: 'Auto-brightness curves' entry under Display → E-Ink Display.
List page shows the three curves and a 'reset all'. Each curve opens
an editor with eight StepperPreference rows (one per lux breakpoint),
plus a 'reset this curve' action.

Change-Id: I14086af2515070278e9afce34cdddd7a1fd4efb6
